PFE Task – Flask App Containerization & CI/CD

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the containerization and deployment of a simple Flask app using Docker, Kubernetes, and GitHub Actions CI 
i can do  terraform but my azure sub is over

**Key features implemented:**

- Multi-stage Dockerfile for a small Flask app
- Docker Compose setup for local testing
- Kubernetes manifests for deployment (Minikube tested)
- GitHub Actions CI workflow:
  - Lints Python code with `flake8`
  - Builds Docker image
  

---

## Project Structure

pfe-task/
│
├─ app/ # Flask app source code
│ ├─ app.py
│ └─ requirements.txt
│
├─ k8s/ # Kubernetes manifests
│ ├─ deployment.yaml
│ └─ service.yaml
│
├─ .github/workflows/ # GitHub Actions CI
│ └─ ci.yml
│
├─ Dockerfile # Multi-stage Dockerfile
├─ docker-compose.yml # Docker Compose setup
├─ README.md
└─ .gitignore


---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/pfe-task.git
cd pfe-task

2. Local Development (Optional)

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r app/requirements.txt

3. Run with Docker Compose

docker-compose up --build

    Access app at: http://localhost:5000/tasks

4. Build & Run Docker Image

docker build -t pfe-task:latest .
docker run -p 5000:5000 pfe-task:latest

5. Kubernetes Deployment (Minikube)

kubectl apply -f k8s/deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/service.yaml
kubectl get pods
minikube service pfe-task-app

GitHub Actions CI/CD

    Runs automatically on push to main branch

    Steps:

        Checkout code

        Install dependencies

        Lint Python code with flake8

        

